# Design Baseline

Generated by `ms-design-baseline` on <YYYY-MM-DD> for Feature <NNN> (first UI surface).
**Single source of truth** for this project's visual design — every later UI task reads the
tokens below and the linked stylesheets instead of hardcoding new values.

## Files

- `tokens.css` — CSS custom properties (global palette → semantic tokens). Edit values here only.
- `base.css` — neutral base stylesheet (typography, forms, buttons, cards, tables) built on the
  tokens above. Import both in that order.

## Palette

| Token | Light | Dark | Use |
|---|---|---|---|
| `--color-bg` | `#ffffff` | `#14171a` | page background |
| `--color-surface` | `#f4f5f7` | `#1e2227` | cards, panels |
| `--color-border` | `#d7dbe0` | `#2a2f36` | dividers, input borders |
| `--color-text` | `#14171a` | `#f4f5f7` | body text (AA, ≥4.5:1 on bg) |
| `--color-muted` | `#5a6472` | `#9aa4b2` | secondary text, labels |
| `--color-accent` | `#1d4ed8` | `#6d8ef7` | links, primary buttons |
| `--color-danger` | `#b91c1c` | `#f87171` | destructive actions, errors |

Dark mode is a **semantic remap** of the same token names (see `tokens.css`'s
`@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` block and the `[data-theme]` override) — never a second,
independently-maintained palette.

## Type scale

System font stack (`-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial,
sans-serif`), 16px body, ~1.25 ratio: `--text-xs` (12.8px) through `--text-3xl` (39px). Body
line-height `1.5`, heading line-height `1.2`.

## Spacing, radius, shadow

4/8-based spacing scale (`--space-1` = 4px … `--space-16` = 64px). Radius steps `--radius-sm`
(4px) / `--radius-md` (8px) / `--radius-lg` (16px) / `--radius-full`. Shadow steps `--shadow-sm`
/ `--shadow-md` / `--shadow-lg`.

## Layout primitives

`.container` (max-width `--container-max`, 1152px), `.stack` (vertical flex, `--gap-stack`),
`.cluster` (wrapping horizontal flex, `--gap-cluster`), `.grid` (auto-fit grid, `--gap-grid`).

## WCAG floors (non-negotiable defaults)

- Body text ≥ 16px (`--text-base`), line-height ≥ 1.5.
- Interactive targets ≥ 44×44px (`--touch-target-min`) — already applied to `button`/`input` in
  `base.css`.
- Text contrast ≥ 4.5:1 against its background (the palette above is chosen to hold this).

## Escalation path

This baseline is the **no-requirements default**, not a ceiling. If the user wants a distinctive
look, hand off to the `frontend-design` plugin skill for aesthetic direction, then record the
outcome back into this file (update the palette/type-scale tables above, not a second competing
document).

